div.div: Actually, I just tried to create custom UDP client for it, idk if its working or not as i haven't tested it yet. However I just found a library that would suit bokusu use case, so yeah, it happened. XD Anyway, if its working well, then bokusu will only proceed to ask for bi-weekly mylist export, official-ish supported with the project (without risking account ban).

Just checked UDP client commands.... it seems kinda impossible to fetch info like what'd you expect from regular anime tracking services through its API, where AniDB would rather list individual episode (similar to Annict, Trakt, TV Time, or IMDb) than individual season (MAL, and the rest of trackers). Now someone looking this issue will ask "Why this impossible?" Well, based on what I understand from UDP Docs, bokusu would need to:
Know what anime already listed from user's "mylist," which in theory already defeats the purpose for being quick as it needs to painfully try to match aid with user's "mylist." Don't forget if there's rate limit, and you can get banned temporarily if something wrong happened with bokusu . Assume if somehow bokusu made a shadow copy of already indexed titles to somewhere, it also need to recursively look any changes from AniDB. And it doesn't seems to have proper filter to begins with. So, it will have same issue as first point. See MYLIST : Retrieve MyList Data.
Now, rather do a really complicated stuff, thankfully AniDB have command to submit export request on MYLISTEXPORT . My idea is, whenever I managed to learn and send UDP command to AniDB, as following:
Login, obviously Check if user have a notification through NOTIFY command If there's any, check any messages that started as "[MY LIST EXPORT]" as title If found, notify user if previous export is finished and beg user to download the export ASAP, and exit the AniDB function to avoid any future issue However, if the message is stale for about 14 days (can be changed between 14-30 days) + {LAST_EXPORTED_DATE} , prompt new export
Send export command Exit the function by logging out
And as you can see, minimum of time for between the export is 14 days. Feel free to give me a better idea to execute this
